{title: Rock of Ages}
{subtitle: Augustus Toplady, 1776 — Hastings tune, 1830}
{key: Eb}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 80}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[Eb]Rock of [Bb]Ages, [Eb]cleft for [Bb]me
[Eb]Let me [Bb]hide my[Eb]self in [Bb]Thee
[Eb]Let the [Bb]water [Cm]and the [Ab]blood
[Eb]From Thy [Bb]riven [Eb]side which [Bb]flowed
[Eb]Be of [Bb]sin the [Cm]double [Ab]cure
[Eb]Cleanse me [Bb]from its [Eb]guilt and [Bb]pow'r[Eb]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[Eb]Not the [Bb]labors [Eb]of my [Bb]hands
[Eb]Can ful[Bb]fill Thy [Eb]law's de[Bb]mands
[Eb]Could my [Bb]zeal no [Cm]respite [Ab]know
[Eb]Could my [Bb]tears for[Eb]ever [Bb]flow
[Eb]All for [Bb]sin could [Cm]not a[Ab]tone
[Eb]Thou must [Bb]save, and [Eb]Thou a[Bb]lone[Eb]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[Eb]Nothing [Bb]in my [Eb]hand I [Bb]bring
[Eb]Simply [Bb]to Thy [Eb]cross I [Bb]cling
[Eb]Naked, [Bb]come to [Cm]Thee for [Ab]dress
[Eb]Helpless, [Bb]look to [Eb]Thee for [Bb]grace
[Eb]Foul, I [Bb]to the [Cm]fountain [Ab]fly
[Eb]Wash me, [Bb]Saviour, [Eb]or I [Bb]die[Eb]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[Eb]While I [Bb]draw this [Eb]fleeting [Bb]breath
[Eb]When my [Bb]eyes shall [Eb]close in [Bb]death
[Eb]When I [Bb]rise to [Cm]worlds un[Ab]known
[Eb]And be[Bb]hold Thee [Eb]on Thy [Bb]throne
[Eb]Rock of [Bb]Ages, [Cm]cleft for [Ab]me
[Eb]Let me [Bb]hide my[Eb]self in [Bb]Thee[Eb]
{end_of_verse}
